 Cala - Police in Cala chased and arrested five suspects after business robbery was reported to them early on Sunday. "It is alleged that number of unknown suspects entered one the business shop early today pointing the owner of business  with firearm demanding money," said police spokesperson, Capt Namhla Mdleleni. "The suspects manage to escape with undisclosed amount of money. "Police followed leads and five suspects, aged between 25 and 39 years, were arrested. "Two firearms -  including a 9mm pistol, and an undisclosed amount of money were recovered." SAPS Cluster Commander for Cofimvaba, Brigadier Nkombisa, strongly commended members for their quick response. "All suspects will appear before Cala Magistrate Court soon facing charges of Business Robbery." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 